  "text": "The CFD dataset was published in [CITATION_1] , and it is composed of 118 RGB images with a resolution of 480 × 320 pixels. All the images are taken using an iPhone 5 from pavements of Beijing, China, which can generally reflect the urban pavement surface condition existing in Beijing. These images have uneven illumination and contain noises such as shadows, oil spots and water stains, which make crack detection quite difficult. We randomly divided 60% (72 images) of the dataset for training and 40% (46 images) of the dataset for testing, as described in [CITATION_2] .",
